This is another email message about Support Ticket #278742942 that was opened yesterday. A second level technician called after I had left for the day and left a message on my voicemail. The original question was about what level of software our WorkCentre 7435 needs to be to work with the Xerox Mobile Print 1.5.1 solution. I found a document on the Xerox Web site called "Supported Printers for Mobile Print 1.51," and it contains a chart that shows the recommended software version for various Xerox devices that .
support Mobile Print 1.5.1. It shows that for a WorkCentre 7435 to support Auto EIP, the software version of the WorkCentre needs to be at 1.222.18. When I print a configuration report on our machine, it shows the Controller+PS ROM version to be at 1.182.18. The person who responded (I think her name was Saye or someting like that -- she didn't spell it out and didn't leave a callback number) left a voice message that the software version 1.182.18 was the correct version for the Mobile Print 1.51.Here are my questions: 1. The document I found on the Xerox Web site, "Supported Printers for Mobile Print 1.5.1", says that Software Version 1.222.18 is the recommended software version for Auto EIP 1.5 or greater for the WorkCentre 7435. Is this version information correct, or is it a mistake? 2. If the version information in the document is a mistake (again, the document specifies version 1.222.18), what is the correct system software version (controller+PS ROM) for our WorkCentre 7435 to be compatible with EIP 1.5? The document "Supported Printers for Mobile Print 1.5.1" says in its first paragraph that "If a machine meets the minimum software version for EIP 1.5, then all settings are configured automatically to enable the machine." This is what we want -- for all settings to be enabled automatically. . ProblemSeverity: SystemOperational . SolutionID: . CaseID: . . Country: USA . . Language: en_US .
